news.title: About 95% of Panaji smart city work near complete: Goa CM
news.para: Earlier this year, even high court judges visited Panaji to understand the problems faced by citizens due to dust pollution in view of the Smart City work.

news.title: Traffic crawls as Panaji smart city works race against deadline
news.para: The shutdown of vital routes, including Mala-Bhatlem and the stretch from St Inez Church to Casa Macau, jammed commuters’ movement.

news.title: Fire audit of hotels, hospitals & commercial buildings in Prayagraj
news.para: ​​​​​Chief Fire Officer (Prayagraj) RK Pandey told TOI that department has roped in as many as 10 teams including two each in Civil Lines and Naini and one each team at Handia, Meja, Phulpur, Soraon, Koraon, and Bara.

news.title: CPC, KITES plan merger to expand footprint in senior living & geriatric care
news.para: KITES Senior Care has a major investor, Dr Ranjan Pai who invested about Rs 60 crore through his family office in two earlier funding rounds, and will hold 35% stake in the merged entity.

news.title: Leasing by Global Capability Centres in India surged 17% in FY24
news.para: In Jan-Mar 2024, GCCs leased ~ 29% of the total office space leased in India. Notably, the total leasing in the GCC segment stood at 4.2 million sq ft in Q4 FY24.

news.title: Credit costs expected to increase if RBI’s proposed norms for projects under construction implemented
news.para: There is a possibility that the implementation of this framework will overlap with the expected credit loss (ECL) framework that is required by RBI.

news.title: BSNL and MTNL prioritise govt organisations for land asset sales worth Rs 1 lakh crore
news.para: Recently, BSNL sold one of its properties in Lucknow to the Income Tax department for around Rs 229 crore, which was the market value of the building.

news.title: Brigade Enterprises posts net profit of Rs 206 crore in Q4 FY24
news.para: Total income rose to Rs 1,762.62 crore in the fourth quarter of the last fiscal from Rs 872.11 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year.

news.title: NBCC reports rise in net profit by 26% in Q4 FY24
news.para: Income from operations rose to Rs 4,024.5 crore in the fourth quarter of the last fiscal as compared to Rs 2,813.35 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: China Evergrande's liquidators seek investors for restructuring
news.para: Earlier this year, China Evergrande, the world's most indebted property developer, was ordered to be liquidated after it was unable to offer a concrete restructuring plan.

news.title: New Zealand tightens some home loan rules
news.para: Banks will need to comply with the new rules from July 1 and the restrictions will apply to new lending for residential properties for both owner-occupiers and investors, the bank said in a statement.

news.title: China's Shenzhen to lower minimum downpayment for first home buyers to 20%
news.para: Shenzhen, a key technology and manufacturing hub, will lower the minimum downpayment required of second home buyers to 30%, the report said.

news.title: Shanghai lowers home downpayments, eases buying curbs
news.para: Shanghai will lower the minimum downpayment ratio for first home purchases to 20%, and cut the ratio for second home purchases to 30% for suburban areas and to 35% for the rest of the city. The new rule will become effective on Tuesday.

news.title: Keystone Realtors raises Rs 800 crore by selling shares to institutional investors
news.para: ​Mumbai-based Keystone Realtors, which sells its properties under Rustomjee brand, informed that the company has allotted 1,21,21,212 equity shares to eligible QIBs at an issue price of Rs 660 per share, totalling Rs 800 crore.

news.title: NCLAT upholds Adani Goodhomes bid with 93% haircut for Radius Estate
news.para: ​A two-member bench comprising the NCLAT Chairman rejected the petitions by two dissenting financial creditors, saying it was "commercial wisdom" of the Committee of Creditors (CoC), which approved the payout to different creditors.

news.title: TARC posts Rs 52 crore net loss in Q4 FY24
news.para: Total income declined 92 per cent to Rs 10.36 crore in the fourth quarter of last fiscal from Rs 135.53 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, according to a regulatory filing on Monday.

news.title: UltraTech Cement offers to acquire 31.6% in UAE-based RAKWCT
news.para: This would be done by UltraTech Cement Middle East Investments Ltd (UCMEIL), a wholly-owned subsidiary of the Indian cement maker in the UAE.

news.title: Yuvraj Singh sends notices to builders for infringement of privacy, delayed home possession
news.para: M/s Brilliant Etoile Private Limited and M/s Uppal Housing Private Limited are the noticees in one of the legal notices pertaining to the delayed possession of the dwelling units.

news.title: Google leases 6,49,000 sq ft office space in Bengaluru
news.para: In 2022, Google Connect Services India Pvt. Ltd, a subsidiary of the US technology conglomerate, had a renewed rental pact for about 600,000 sq ft office space in Hyderabad.

news.title: Godrej & Boyce sells 58,500 sq ft office space in Mumbai’s Vikhroli to Godrej Industries
news.para: The office space on the 9th floor has already been leased to managed flexible workspace provider Simpliwork Offices for a period of 60 months until March 31, 2026. This lease will also be transferred to Godrej industries as the new landlord, showed the documents accessed through Propstack.
